result.execSummary:
Cole H. Gudmundsen was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Cole H. Gudmundsen was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Rosa Delgado appeared for the State.  Defendant in custody and appeared in court w/ Attorney Donald Bielski (in 14CF94) & Attorney David Celebre (in 14CF202).  Clerk: MHerr.
MINUTES:  9:48am-  Matter heard with 14CF94.  DE waives his right to an extradition hearing.  Waiver is signed by the DE and the Court.  Court orders the DE be retained in the Kenosha Co Jail until he is sentenced in 14CF94.
Attorney Celebre is requesting 3/27/2014 Extradition hearing be rescheduled due to scheduling conflict.  Extradition hearing is rescheduled to 4/14/2014 at 9am.  Parties notified via email.
